# Goals

> AutoForge Agents module enables spec-driven serial cooperation of profession-bearing AI agents, maximizing quality and token efficiency through relay orchestration.


## Goals

| ID | Goal | Priority | Status | Stakeholder |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| G1 | Agent Identity System supports Soul, Profession, and Model configuration per agent | P0 | Done | Tooling Team |
| G2 | Relay Orchestrator executes serial agent flows with baton passing and gate enforcement | P0 | Implemented | Tooling Team |
| G3 | Handoff Protocol compresses context between agents, achieving ~5× token savings vs parallel multi-agent | P0 | Implemented | Tooling Team |
| G4 | Checkpoint & Durability system enables long-running flows to survive crashes and resume without context loss | P0 | Implemented | Tooling Team |
| G5 | Token Budgeting tracks and enforces per-step spend with cost analytics visible in Agents view | P1 | Implemented | Tooling Team |
| G6 | Boss-first execution: GSD mode runs autonomously with optional Check mode for gate review | P0 | Done | Tooling Team |
| G7 | Spec pyramid supports Goals → Architecture → Designs → Plans → Tests → Reviews → Reports with no APIs category | P0 | Done | Tooling Team |
| G8 | Chat-First Gate Approval with Smart Secretary | P0 | Implemented | UI Team |
| G9 | Specs Workspace with Bidirectional Traceability | P0 | Implemented | UI Team |
| G10 | Live Relay Pipeline Visualization | P0 | Implemented | UI Team |
| G11 | Responsive and Accessible Frontend | P1 | Implemented | UI Team |
| G12 | Project Concept enables VS Code–style folder opening with persistent workspace | P0 | Done | Core Team |
| G13 | API Source Configuration supports multi-provider LLM management with auto-detection and model tiers | P0 | Proposed | Core Team |
| G14 | Unified Provider Layer consolidates AI communication from auto-code-rs into provider/ module with SSE streaming | P0 | Done | Core Team |
| G15 | CLI Mode provides interactive REPL chat as forge chat subcommand | P1 | Removed | Core Team |

